    <title type="text">New Open Access Journal: HIPHIL Novum</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a href="http://www.hiphil.org/index.php/hiphil/index">HIPHIL
      Novum</a><br /><div><div><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><strong>HIPHIL Novum</strong> is a peer-reviewed
      academic e-journal publishing on global education and research on the Bible. Issues feature
      papers accepted by Society of Biblical Literature's Program Unit <strong>GERT - <a
      href="http://sbl-site.org/meetings/Congresses_CallForPaperDetails.aspx?MeetingId=25&amp;VolunteerUnitId=634">Global
      Education and Reseach Technology</a></strong> as well as other papers on next
      generation biblical research. We want to promote open education for all continents, races,
      genders, and communities.</span><br /><div><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><strong>HIPHIL</strong> Novum publishes papers on research or projecs
      focusing on the Bible's<strong>
      </strong></span></div><div><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><strong> H</strong>istory&nbsp; *&nbsp;
      <strong>I</strong>nterpretation&nbsp; *
      <strong>P</strong>edagogy<strong> * H</strong>ermeneutics<strong>
      * I</strong>nteractive Technology *&nbsp;
      <strong>L</strong>inguistics</span></div><div><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">HIPHIL is <strong>Novum</strong> - the focus is on
      new Biblical Studies for a digital and global age. We welcome papers that take a lead in
      emerging global 21st Century education.</span></div><div><div><span
      style="font-size:
      x-small;"><strong>EDITORIAL</strong></span></div><div><ul><li><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">Editor: Nicolai Winther-Nielsen and his assistants Randall Tan
      (New Testamaent), David Kummerow (Hebrew Bible) and Jens Bruun Kofoed (history theory).
      </span></li><li><span style="font-size: x-small;">Board, at upstar:
      Kirk Lowery, Joshua Berman and Wido van Peursen</span></li><li><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">Peer reviewers: members of the advisory group of <a
      href="http://biblicalhumanities.org/"
      title="Biblicalhumanities.org">Biblicalhumanities.org/</a> and individual scholars.
      </span></li></ul></div></div><div><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">HIPHIL Novum
      publishes</span></div><ul><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><strong>Peer-reviewed articles</strong>: normally 7500 words,
      occasionally longer. One other competent researcher must approve the quality of this research
      before publication. </span></li><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><strong>Conference papers</strong>: normally 2500 words, acceptance
      based on public presentation.</span></li><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><strong>Reports: </strong>News on projects, dissertations or unique
      studies of global relevance. </span></li><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><strong>Reviews</strong>: Promotion of books or digital
      ressources</span></li></ul><h4><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a href="http://www.hiphil.org/index.php/hiphil/issue/view/8">Vol 1, No 1
